messages.message:
Hi all,

I have this PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/47814) that I'd like to get in for 23.10, but is failing some typechecking (https://jenkins.instabase.com/job/instabase/job/PR-47814/2/console) unrelated to my changes.
```Name 'long' is not defined```
Has anyone else seen this? Someone on my team ran into the same issue but it was resolved after rerunning CI. This error persists for me after rerunning.

this is an actual error... cc @Heymian since this is related to account. `long` has become `int` in Python 3.X, how these errors went away after rerunning CI is problematic. I did a quick code search and these are all very old code written years ago. @Jag can you make a quick PR that change all
`# type: long`
to be
`# type: int`
in the codebase (do a quick search and replace). Tag me as reviewer, I'll review and merge the PR.

Heymain, let me know if you have any concerns? cc @shaunak here on potential CI problem
Yep will put up a PR
no concern, we should fix. thanks Jag!

Here's the long->int PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/47970) btw.

Interestingly the PR that was being blocked by these failures eventually just passed after a few reruns of CI.
i approved and merged. Thank you.
